file.content:
openapi: 3.0.1
info:
  title: Prime Developer Trial
  version: v1
servers:
- url: https://api.factset.com/wealth/v1
security:
- FactSetApiKey: []
- FactSetOAuth2: []
tags:
- description: debtInstrument endpoints
  name: debtInstrument
paths:
  /debtInstrument/get:
    get:
      description: Fundamental data for a debt instrument; any other instrument yields
        empty values for debt-instrument-specific attributes. Dates are interpreted
        in the timezone of the issuer.
      operationId: get/debtInstrument/get
      parameters:
      - description: Identifier of the instrument.
        in: query
        name: id
        required: true
        schema:
          format: id64
          type: string
          x-positive: true
        x-positive: true
      - description: Limit the attributes returned in the response to the specified
          set.
        explode: false
        in: query
        name: _attributes
        schema:
          items:
            maxLength: 100
            type: string
          maxItems: 50
          type: array
          uniqueItems: true
        style: form
      - description: ISO 639-1 code of the language.
        in: query
        name: _language
        schema:
          exclusiveMaximum: false
          exclusiveMinimum: false
          format: isoLanguage
          maxLength: 2
          minLength: 2
          type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200'
          description: Successful Response
      summary: Fundamental data for a debt instrument.
      tags:
      - debtInstrument
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPaging: false
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPaging: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsPush: false
      x-requiresUser: false
      x-requiresInternalClient: false
      x-disallowUser: false
      x-no-merge: false
      x-maxSortParameterCount: 10
      x-supportsPermissionDeniedResponse: false
      x-accepts: application/json
  /debtInstrument/issuer/search:
    post:
      description: Search for issuers of debt instruments. FactSet does not consolidate
        the data provided by different suppliers, therefore the result may contain
        more than one identifier for a given issuer. The response is limited to 100
        results.
      operationId: post/debtInstrument/issuer/search
      requestBody:
        $ref: '#/components/requestBodies/inline_object'
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              properties:
                data:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/_debtInstrument_issuer_search_data'
                meta:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/_debtInstrument_issuer_search_meta'
              type: object
              x-property-sort:
              - data
              - meta
        required: false
      responses:
        "200":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_1'
          description: Successful Response
      summary: Search for issuers of debt instruments.
      tags:
      - debtInstrument
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPaging: false
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPaging: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsPush: false
      x-requiresUser: false
      x-requiresInternalClient: false
      x-disallowUser: false
      x-no-merge: false
      x-maxSortParameterCount: 10
      x-supportsPermissionDeniedResponse: false
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
      x-contentType: application/json
      x-accepts: application/json
  /debtInstrument/keyFigures/notation/get:
    get:
      description: Key figures of a debt instrument. The key figures are calculated
        using delayed prices with an additional delay of 10 minutes after an  update
        of the debt instrument's price. Special product features such as the right
        to a maturity extension, an attached option, or convertibility are not considered
        for the key figure calculation. Further, a calculation is not performed for
        perpetual products and for products with variable interest rate.
      operationId: get/debtInstrument/keyFigures/notation/get
      parameters:
      - description: Identifier of a notation.
        in: query
        name: id
        required: true
        schema:
          format: id64
          type: string
          x-positive: true
        x-positive: true
      - description: Limit the attributes returned in the response to the specified
          set.
        explode: false
        in: query
        name: _attributes
        schema:
          items:
            maxLength: 100
            type: string
          maxItems: 50
          type: array
          uniqueItems: true
        style: form
      responses:
        "200":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_2'
          description: Successful Response
      summary: Key figures of a debt instrument.
      tags:
      - debtInstrument
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPaging: false
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPaging: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsPush: false
      x-requiresUser: false
      x-requiresInternalClient: false
      x-disallowUser: false
      x-no-merge: false
      x-maxSortParameterCount: 10
      x-supportsPermissionDeniedResponse: false
      x-accepts: application/json
  /debtInstrument/notation/screener/search:
    post:
      description: Screener for debt instruments' notations based on debt instrument-specific
        parameters. The result is limited to the notations that satisfy all the selected
        filters. If more than one notation of an instrument matches the parameters,
        and no market priority has been specified, only the notation with the highest
        trading volume, averaged over one month, is considered.
      operationId: post/debtInstrument/notation/screener/search
      requestBody:
        $ref: '#/components/requestBodies/inline_object_1'
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              properties:
                data:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/_debtInstrument_notation_screener_search_data'
                meta:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/_debtInstrument_notation_screener_search_meta'
              type: object
              x-property-sort:
              - data
              - meta
        required: false
      responses:
        "200":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_3'
          description: Successful Response
      summary: Screener for debt instruments' notations based on debt instrument-specific
        parameters.
      tags:
      - debtInstrument
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPaging: true
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPaging: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsPush: false
      x-requiresUser: false
      x-requiresInternalClient: false
      x-disallowUser: false
      x-no-merge: false
      x-maxSortParameterCount: 10
      x-supportsPermissionDeniedResponse: false
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
      x-contentType: application/json
      x-accepts: application/json
  /debtInstrument/notation/screener/valueRanges/get:
    post:
      description: The endpoint returns the possible values and value ranges for the
        parameters used in the endpoint `/debtInstrument/notation/screener/search`.
        It allows to request the values and value ranges only for a restricted set
        of notations that match predefined parameters. The functionality may be used
        to pre-fill the values and value ranges of the parameters of the `/debtInstrument/notation/screener/search`
        endpoint so that performing a search always leads to a non-empty set of notations.
        If more than one notation of an instrument matches the parameters, and no
        market priority has been specified, only the notation with the highest trading
        volume, averaged over one month, is considered.
      operationId: post/debtInstrument/notation/screener/valueRanges/get
      requestBody:
        $ref: '#/components/requestBodies/inline_object_2'
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              properties:
                data:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/_debtInstrument_notation_screener_valueRanges_get_data'
                meta:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/_debtInstrument_notation_screener_valueRanges_get_meta'
              type: object
              x-property-sort:
              - data
              - meta
        required: false
      responses:
        "200":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_4'
          description: Successful Response
      summary: Possible values and value ranges for the parameters used in the endpoint
        `/debtInstrument/notation/screener/search.`
      tags:
      - debtInstrument
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPaging: false
      x-supportsOffsetBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPaging: false
      x-supportsCursorBasedPagingWithoutTotal: false
      x-supportsPush: false
      x-requiresUser: false
      x-requiresInternalClient: false
      x-disallowUser: false
      x-no-merge: false
      x-maxSortParameterCount: 10
      x-supportsPermissionDeniedResponse: false
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
      x-contentType: application/json
      x-accepts: application/json
components:
  requestBodies:
    inline_object_1:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_object_1'
      required: false
    inline_object:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_object'
      required: false
    inline_object_2:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_object_2'
      required: false
  responses:
    ErrorResponse:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            properties:
              meta:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorMetaObject'
              errors:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorObject'
            type: object
      description: Generic error response for all errors (400 ... 599 error codes)
  schemas:
    ErrorMetaObject:
      properties:
        status:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/StatusObject'
      type: object
    ErrorObject:
      description: The errors member contains additional information about a failed
        request.
      items:
        properties:
          details:
            description: A human-readable, unstructured explanation specific to this
              occurrence of the failure.
            type: string
          encryptedDetails:
            description: Base64-encoded, internal details about the error, in addition
              to "details".
            type: string
          type:
            description: Internal error type of the Foundation API protocol.
            format: int32
            type: number
          attribute:
            description: For a validation error, a reference to the request parameter
              that failed validation; otherwise, an empty array.
            items:
              properties:
                name:
                  description: Element of the path denoting the request parameter.
                  type: string
                index:
                  description: If the attribute "name" designates an array, index
                    of the array element; otherwise the special value -1.
                  format: int32
                  type: number
              type: object
              x-property-sort:
              - name
              - index
            type: array
        type: object
        x-property-sort:
        - detail
        - encryptedDetails
        - type
        - attribute
      type: array
    AttributesMember:
      description: Limit the attributes returned in the response to the specified
        set.
      items:
        maxLength: 100
        type: string
      maxItems: 50
      type: array
      uniqueItems: true
    LanguageMember:
      description: ISO 639-1 code of the language.
      exclusiveMaximum: false
      exclusiveMinimum: false
      format: isoLanguage
      maxLength: 2
      minLength: 2
      type: string
    StatusObject:
      description: The status member contains the status code of the response.
      example:
        code: 1.2315135367772556
      properties:
        code:
          description: The HTTP status code of the response, mirroring the code from
            the Status-Line of the HTTP response message (see [RFC2616] section 6.1).
          format: int32
          type: number
      required:
      - code
      type: object
    CursorBasedPaginationOutputObject:
      description: Pagination attributes for the cursor-based pagination strategy.
      properties:
        total:
          description: Total number of entries in the result set.
          format: int32
          type: number
        isEstimatedTotal:
          description: Flag indicating that the value of `total` is estimated.
          type: boolean
        next:
          description: The next cursor position to use in the parameter `pagination.cursor`
            for an endpoint that supports cursor-based pagination, otherwise `null`.
          type: string
        previous:
          description: The previous cursor position to use in the parameter `pagination.cursor`
            for an endpoint that supports cursor-based pagination. If a previous cursor
            position is not supported or available, `previous` is `null`.
          type: string
      required:
      - isEstimatedTotal
      - next
      - previous
      - total
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - total
      - isEstimatedTotal
      - next
      - previous
    CursorBasedPaginationOutputObjectWithoutTotal:
      description: Pagination attributes for the cursor-based pagination strategy;
        a total element count is not supported.
      properties:
        next:
          description: The next cursor position to use in the parameter `pagination.cursor`
            for an endpoint that supports cursor-based pagination, otherwise `null`.
          type: string
        previous:
          description: The previous cursor position to use in the parameter `pagination.cursor`
            for an endpoint that supports cursor-based pagination. If a previous cursor
            position is not supported or available, `previous` is `null`.
          type: string
      required:
      - next
      - previous
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - next
      - previous
    OffsetBasedPaginationOutputObject:
      description: Pagination attributes for the offset-based pagination strategy.
      example:
        total: 9.018348186070783
        isEstimatedTotal: true
      properties:
        total:
          description: Total number of entries in the result set.
          format: int32
          type: number
        isEstimatedTotal:
          description: Flag indicating that the value of "total" is estimated.
          type: boolean
      required:
      - isEstimatedTotal
      - total
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - total
      - isEstimatedTotal
    OffsetBasedPaginationOutputObjectWithoutTotal:
      description: Pagination attributes for the offset-based pagination strategy;
        a total element count is not supported.
      properties:
        hasNext:
          description: Flag indicating that a subsequent request with the same parameters,
            except that the parameter `pagination.offset` is incremented by `pagination.limit`,
            would yield additional results.
          type: boolean
      required:
      - hasNext
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - hasNext
    PartialOutputObject:
      description: Object denoting that the endpoint response is possibly incomplete.
      example:
        isPartial: true
      properties:
        isPartial:
          description: Flag indicating that the response is a possibly incomplete
            array or an object containing a possibly incomplete array, due to hitting
            a processing time limit. If `true`, some matching results might be missing
            from the array, or elements for matching results might be incorrectly
            included (for example, when priority sorting would have removed the element).
            Depending on the use case, such a response may be unsuitable.
          type: boolean
      required:
      - isPartial
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - isPartial
    inline_response_200_data_nsin:
      description: NSIN data of the instrument.
      example:
        valor: valor
        wkn: wkn
      properties:
        wkn:
          description: The WKN (Wertpapierkennnummer, German for Securities Identification
            Number) of the instrument. The WKN is a 6-character code of digits and
            upper-case letters that uniquely identifies an instrument.
          type: string
        valor:
          description: 'The Valor number (German: Valorennummer) of the instrument.
            The Valor number is an integer number that uniquely identifies an instrument.'
          type: string
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - wkn
      - valor
    inline_response_200_data_type:
      example:
        name: name
        id: 0.8008281904610115
      properties:
        id:
          description: Identifier of the instrument type.
          format: id32
          type: number
          x-positive: true
        name:
          description: Name of the instrument type.
          format: localizedString
          type: string
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - id
      - name
    inline_response_200_data_lifeCycle_maturity:
      description: Maturity data.
      example:
        date: 2000-01-23
        isCallable: true
        isPerpetual: true
      properties:
        date:
          description: Date of the instrument's maturity. The value is empty if the
            instrument is perpetual.
          format: date
          type: string
        isPerpetual:
          description: If true, the instrument is perpetual, i.e. it does not mature,
            therefore the attribute `date` is null.
          type: boolean
        isCallable:
          description: If true, the issuer may redeem the instrument prior to maturity.
          type: boolean
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - date
      - isPerpetual
      - isCallable
    inline_response_200_data_lifeCycle:
      description: Important dates of the instrument.
      example:
        issue: 2000-01-23
        maturity:
          date: 2000-01-23
          isCallable: true
          isPerpetual: true
      properties:
        issue:
          description: Date of the issue.
          format: date
          type: string
        maturity:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_data_lifeCycle_maturity'
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - issue
      - maturity
    inline_response_200_data_issuer:
      description: Issuer of the instrument. See endpoint `/legalEntity/list` for
        possible values.
      example:
        lei: lei
        name: name
        id: id
      properties:
        id:
          description: Identifier of the issuer.
          format: id64
          type: string
          x-positive: true
        name:
          description: Name of the issuer.
          type: string
        lei:
          description: Legal Entity Identifier of the issuer.
          type: string
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - id
      - name
      - lei
    inline_response_200_data_issue_price_valueUnit:
      description: Value unit of the issue price such as percentages for a debt instrument
        quoted in percent, or a main or a fractional currency for a per-unit-quoted
        debt instrument (rarely). See endpoint `/basic/valueUnit/list` for possible
        values.
      example:
        code: code
        id: 1.4658129805029452
      properties:
        id:
          description: Identifier of the value unit.
          format: id32
          type: number
          x-positive: true
        code:
          description: Code of the value unit.
          type: string
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - id
      - code
    inline_response_200_data_issue_price:
      description: Issue price data.
      example:
        valueUnit:
          code: code
          id: 1.4658129805029452
        value: 6.027456183070403
      properties:
        value:
          description: Issue price.
          format: real
          type: number
        valueUnit:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_data_issue_price_valueUnit'
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - value
      - valueUnit
    inline_response_200_data_issue_volume_currency:
      description: Main currency of denomination of the issue volume. See endpoint
        `/basic/valueUnit/currency/main/list` for possible values.
      example:
        code: code
        isoCode: isoCode
        id: 5.637376656633329
      properties:
        id:
          description: Identifier of the currency.
          format: id32
          type: number
          x-positive: true
        code:
          description: 'Code of the currency: if assigned, a code according to ISO
            4217, otherwise a local code.'
          type: string
        isoCode:
          description: ISO 4217 code of the currency.
          type: string
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - id
      - code
      - isoCode
    inline_response_200_data_issue_volume:
      description: Issue volume data.
      example:
        amount: 5.962133916683182
        currency:
          code: code
          isoCode: isoCode
          id: 5.637376656633329
      properties:
        amount:
          description: Issue volume.
          format: real
          type: number
        currency:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_data_issue_volume_currency'
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - amount
      - currency
    inline_response_200_data_issue:
      description: Issue data of the instrument.
      example:
        volume:
          amount: 5.962133916683182
          currency:
            code: code
            isoCode: isoCode
            id: 5.637376656633329
        price:
          valueUnit:
            code: code
            id: 1.4658129805029452
          value: 6.027456183070403
      properties:
        price:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_data_issue_price'
        volume:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_data_issue_volume'
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - price
      - volume
    inline_response_200_data_tradingVolume:
      description: Requirements regarding the trading volume in the over-the-counter
        (non-exchange-based) trading. For the currency of the trading volume, see
        attribute `issue.volume.currency`.
      example:
        increment: 7.061401241503109
        minimum: 2.3021358869347655
      properties:
        minimum:
          description: Minimum trading volume.
          format: real
          type: number
        increment:
          description: Incremental trading volume over the minimum. The trading volume
            over the minimum must be an integral multiple of the increment.
          format: real
          type: number
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - minimum
      - increment
    inline_response_200_data_redemption_price_valueUnit:
      description: Value unit of the redemption price such as percentages for a debt
        instrument quoted in percent, or a main or a fractional currency for a per-unit-quoted
        debt instrument (rarely). See endpoint `/basic/valueUnit/list` for possible
        values.
      example:
        code: code
        id: 3.616076749251911
      properties:
        id:
          description: Identifier of the value unit.
          format: id32
          type: number
          x-positive: true
        code:
          description: Code of the value unit.
          type: string
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - id
      - code
    inline_response_200_data_redemption_price:
      description: Redemption price data.
      example:
        valueUnit:
          code: code
          id: 3.616076749251911
        value: 9.301444243932576
      properties:
        value:
          description: Redemption price.
          format: real
          type: number
        valueUnit:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_data_redemption_price_valueUnit'
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - value
      - valueUnit
    inline_response_200_data_redemption_currency:
      description: Main currency of the redemption. See endpoint `/basic/valueUnit/currency/main/list`
        for possible values.
      example:
        code: code
        isoCode: isoCode
        id: 2.027123023002322
      properties:
        id:
          description: Identifier of the currency.
          format: id32
          type: number
          x-positive: true
        code:
          description: 'Code of the currency: if assigned, a code according to ISO
            4217, otherwise a local code.'
          type: string
        isoCode:
          description: ISO 4217 code of the currency.
          type: string
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - id
      - code
      - isoCode
    inline_response_200_data_redemption:
      description: Redemption data of the instrument.
      example:
        price:
          valueUnit:
            code: code
            id: 3.616076749251911
          value: 9.301444243932576
        currency:
          code: code
          isoCode: isoCode
          id: 2.027123023002322
      properties:
        price:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_data_redemption_price'
        currency:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_data_redemption_currency'
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - price
      - currency
    inline_response_200_data_debtRanking:
      description: Ranking data of the debt instrument. It indicates how payments
        related to the debt instrument are ranked  compared to payments on the issuer's
        other obligations.
      example:
        name: name
        id: 7.386281948385884
      properties:
        id:
          description: Identifier of the debt ranking.
          format: id32
          type: number
          x-positive: true
        name:
          description: Name of the debt ranking.
          format: localizedString
          type: string
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - id
      - name
    inline_response_200_data_germany:
      description: Specific data for Germany.
      example:
        isTrusteeEligible: true
      properties:
        isTrusteeEligible:
          description: If true, the debt instrument is eligible for investments by
            trustees according to §§1806ff of the BGB (German Civil Code). The German
            legislative has declared it to be virtually free of the risk of loss,
            such as government and state bonds. Eligible are primarily German securities.
          type: boolean
      type: object
      x-property-sort:
      - isTrusteeEligible
    inline_response_200_data:
      description: Fundamental data for a debt instrument.
      example:
        issue:
          volume:
            amount: 5.962133916683182
            currency:
              code: code
              isoCode: isoCode
              id: 5.637376656633329
          price:
            valueUnit:
              code: code
              id: 1.4658129805029452
            value: 6.027456183070403
        germany:
          isTrusteeEligible: true
        type:
        - name: name
          id: 0.8008281904610115
        - name: name
          id: 0.8008281904610115
        debtRanking:
          name: name
          id: 7.386281948385884
        tradingVolume:
          increment: 7.061401241503109
          minimum: 2.3021358869347655
        issuer:
          lei: lei
          name: name
          id: id
        redemption:
          price:
            valueUnit:
              code: code
              id: 3.616076749251911
            value: 9.301444243932576
          currency:
            code: code
            isoCode: isoCode
            id: 2.027123023002322
